# Intuition Engine x64 Live Image

This directory is the staging area for the bootable x64 live image built by
`make x64-live`.

The appliance image starts Intuition Engine at the EhBASIC `Ready` prompt with
the BASIC `HOST` helper path and appliance update mode enabled for controlled
host maintenance commands. Host command execution is gated in the emulator by
`-ehbasic-host`; normal desktop runs leave execution disabled unless that flag
is supplied.

## Firewall Baseline

The live image firewall baseline is default deny for incoming traffic and
default allow for outgoing traffic. The intended shipped unit is
`ie-firewall.service`, a one-shot service that enables ufw with that policy at
boot.

`HOST NET` must not open inbound ports or change the default incoming policy.
After network configuration, `ufw status verbose` should still report active
ufw with incoming denied and outgoing allowed.

## Host Helper

The privileged helper binary is expected at
`/usr/libexec/intuitionengine-host-helper`. PolicyKit and AppArmor rules should
grant only the fixed helper action required by Intuition Engine, not a general
root shell or broad NetworkManager access for the `ie` user.
